Japan Chemical Industry Ecology - Toxicology and Information Center. ISBN 4-89074-101-1 p. 3-9 (1992) (2) Franke C et al; Chemosphere 29: 1501-14 (1994)
environmental_bioconcentrations.Value: BCFs of 70-160 were obtained in Carp for 5-ethylidene-2-norbornene in an eight-week screening test. According to a classification scheme(2), these BCFs suggest the potential for bioconcentration in aquatic organisms is moderate to high.

environmental_biodegradations.References: (1) Chemicals Inspection and Testing Institute; Biodegradation and Bioaccumulation Data of Existing Chemicals Based on the CSCL Japan. Japan Chemical Industry Ecology - Toxicology and Information Center. ISBN 4-89074-101-1 p. 3-9 (1992)
environmental_biodegradations.Value: AEROBIC: 5-Ethylidene-2-norbornene, at a concentration of 100 mg/l, reached 0% of its theoretical BOD over 4 weeks using a mixed inoculum of sludge, soil, and sediment in the Japanese MITI test(1).

non_human_toxicity_excerpts.Value: CHRONIC INHALATION EXPOSURES: RENAL LESIONS OCCURRED IN RATS AT 90 OR 237 PPM & AT HIGHER DOSE LIVER LESIONS. AT CONCN OF 61 OR 93 PPM FOR 7 HR/DAY FOR 89 DAYS, HEPATIC LESIONS OBSERVED IN DOGS.
INHALATION OF 61 PPM FOR 7 HR DAILY FOR 88 DAYS DECR WT GAIN IN MALE, BUT NOT FEMALE RATS, WHEREAS WT GAINS IN DOGS WERE NOT AFFECTED BY 1.5 TIMES THIS CONCENTRATION.

non_human_toxicity_excerpts.References: American Conference of Governmental Industrial Hygienists, Inc. Documentation of the Threshold Limit Values and Biological Exposure Indices. 6th ed. Volumes I, II, III. Cincinnati, OH: ACGIH, 1991., p. 635
non_human_toxicity_excerpts.Value: BEAGLE DOGS SURVIVED 89 ... 7-HOUR EXPOSURES AT 93 PPM, BUT SHOWED A VARIETY OF EFFECTS, INCL TESTICULAR ATROPHY, HEPATIC LESIONS AND SLIGHT BLOOD CHANGES. LESS MARKED EFFECTS WERE NOTED AT 61 PPM, AND NONE WERE OBSERVED AT 22 PPM.
ETHYLIDENENORBORNENE WAS SLIGHTLY TOXIC BY DERMAL ROUTE & MODERATELY TOXIC BY ORAL ROUTE IN SINGLE DOSE STUDIES IN RATS, RABBITS, MICE, DOGS.

NECROSIS FOLLOWING APPLICATION TO RAT SKIN. INHALATION OF 0.11-0.43 MG/L BY MICE OR RATS 4 HR/DAY FOR 7-12.5 WK DECR SOPORIFIC EFFECTS OF HEXENAL & CAUSED MORPHOLOGICAL CHANGES IN HEART, LIVER & ENDOCRINE GLANDS. HORMONAL DYSFUNCTION OF OVARIES IN FEMALE RATS.

non_human_toxicity_excerpts.References: Zeiger E et al; Environ Mutagen 9: 1-110 (1987)
non_human_toxicity_excerpts.Value: Ethylidene norbornene (EN) was tested for mutagenicity in the Salmonella/microsome preincubation assay using a protocol approved by the National Toxicology Program. EN was tested over a wide range of doses (0, 3, 10, 33, 100, and 333 ug/plate) in four Salmonella typhimurium strains (TA98, TA100, TA1535, and TA1537) in the presence and absence of Aroclor-induced rat or hamster liver S9. EN was negative in these tests and the highest ineffective dose level tested (without causing a slight clearing of the background lawn) in any Salmonella tester strain was 100 ug/plate.

soil_absorption_mobility.References: (1) Meylan WM et al; Environ Sci Technol 26: 1560-67 (1992) (2) Swann RL et al; Res Rev 85: 23 (1983)
soil_absorption_mobility.Value: Using a structure estimation method based on molecular connectivity indices(1), the Koc for 5-ethylidene-2-norbornene is estimated to be 900(SRC). According to a classification scheme(2), this estimated Koc value suggests that 5-ethylidene-2-norbornene is expected to have low mobility in soil.
